<subSubSection pageId="79" pageNumber="563" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="79.[735,1328,2733,3157]" lastBlockId="79.[120,1186,3163,3196]" pageId="79" pageNumber="563">
Within three weeks of this description, C. ©. Handley, Jv. and KR. C. Ferris in 1972 described Vampyrops latus, and after comparisons, it was deemed to be a junior synonym. Nevertheless, subspecies V. latus saccharus by the same authors is considered distinct. For a long time, 
<taxonomicName box="[1104,1328,3124,3157]" family="Solanaceae" genus="Platyrrhainus" pageId="79" pageNumber="563" rank="species" species="brachycephalus">P. brachycephalus</taxonomicName>
was confused with 
<taxonomicName box="[384,491,3163,3196]" class="Insecta" family="Anthribidae" genus="Platyrrhinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="79" pageNumber="563" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="helleri">P. helleri</taxonomicName>
or its associated taxa. Two subspecies recognized.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
